com.wx.properties

Class PropertiesManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wx.properties.PropertiesManager
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ResourcePage

    public class PropertiesManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This class enhances any PropertiesMapInterface by providing advanced features such as the ability to store many types, including lists, maps, etc...

    It also allows to store null values independently of the underlying PropertiesMapInterface implementation.

    In order to provide theses features, this manager comes with a set of limitations. Mainly, it uses constructs such as ${...} to encode commands. Thus, to avoid unexpected behaviour, values should not contains that pattern of characters.

      • setProperties

        public <E> void setProperties(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,E> properties,
                              java.util.function.Function<E,java.lang.String> caster)
        Set a whole map of properties. This will add all the properties contained in the given map.

        Note: Do not confuse this with setMap(java.lang.String, java.util.Map<K, V>, com.wx.util.representables.TypeCaster<java.lang.String, K>, com.wx.util.representables.TypeCaster<java.lang.String, V>, com.wx.properties.structures.Structures, java.lang.String...) that will associate a map to a single key.

        Type Parameters:
        E - Type of the properties (must be the same for all properties)
        Parameters:
        properties - The keys - values to set.
        caster - Caster to represent the value into a String
